Policy: Configure Azure Activity logs to stream to specified Log Analytics workspace
Policy ID: 2465583e-4e78-4c15-b6be-a36cbc7c8b0f

What this policy DOES

Creates diagnostic settings at subscription scope
Streams Azure Activity Logs (control‑plane events) to Log Analytics workspace (LAW)
Applies automatically using DeployIfNotExists

After this policy:

Logs are sent out of the Activity Log service
Logs arrive in Log Analytics (table: AzureActivity)


Policy: Activity log should be retained for at least one year
Policy ID: b02aacc0-b073-424e-8298-42b22829ee0a

This is an AuditIfNotExists policy. It checks whether, Activity Logs are configured to be retained for ≥ 365 days OR forever. It does not create or move logs anywhere, it's purely for Audit only.

So the actual retention happens only in the destination (Log Analytics Workspace or Storage Account), where retention must be explicitly configured.  It is recommended to take LAW,

Step 1: Open the Log Analytics workspace

Azure Portal
Search Log Analytics workspaces
Select your central logging workspace

Step 2: Go to Tables

In the workspace menu → Tables
Ensure Analytics tab is selected
Search for: AzureActivity

Step 3: Configure retention for AzureActivity

Click AzureActivity
Click Settings
Set:

Retention (days) → 365 (regulated)
or 90 (non‑regulated)
Optionally enable Archive for long‑term retention (up to 12 years)

Example:
Analytics retention: 365 days
Archive retention: 2555 days (optional)
